      <div class ="journey-core">
        <h2 class="journey-title">My historical journey</h2>
        <p class="journey-text">I studied work law until I obtain my Master then I studied one more year in a Business School to be more
        specialized in Human Resources.
        Thanks to that I worked as a specialist recruter and was focused on finding people for Industry's companies.
        The lack of skilled trades people in specific trades are factors to the intensity of this work, what makes it a
        challenging opportunity and in the same time a way to increase my versatility, from professional understanding of
        industry's needs to ability to answer every client's request by searching, interviewing and send candidates (among other things).
        Two years later I switch to another company, more of a start up, and that's when I discovered a new way of work, modern and
        open to the new technology possibilities. Working in a team, I was more focused on the client's side
        and a way to help them in their specific needs and issues,
        in a faster way, all in teaching my recruter's team how to deal with the complixity of the customer request and report weekly
        about the market evolution to the direction.
        That is also where I discover what is a Product Manager and what does he do. <br>
        After two years, without anything more to discover and stuck in my position, I wanted to start my own company so
        I decided to quit.
        I struggled a little, needed money that I didn't have, get disappointed trying to do it the old way.
        Meanwhile I talked to some of my friends who are working in tech companies and understood that the futur is in this way.
        I went to Le Wagon bootcamp and learned to code in Ruby, to use Ruby on Rails and drive a project. After 9 weeks, I decided
        with some other alumni to improve our skills and practice what we learned, each one on a specific interest for their futur.
        Crushs was born ! We set a time limit of 6 months, my part was really focused on the PM duty whereas I learn from scratch
        how to deal with this job.
        In the same time, I tried on my own to build a markeplace in fashion with a specific vision.
        And that's it !
        </p>
